cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about analyzing the representations learned by a deep neural network for natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the decision rules learned by the network, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper uses diagnostic tests to evaluate the network's performance, which is a common technique in machine learning, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the effect of training distribution on learning, which is a topic in neural networks, suggesting that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions augmentations to the training set, which is a common technique in computer vision, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
